---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const lastUpdated = '2026-01-19';
---

<Layout title="Terms of Service | PkgWatch" mainClass="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-24 pt-32">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Terms of Service</h1>
    <p class="text-zinc-400 mb-8">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>

    <div class="prose prose-invert prose-zinc max-w-none space-y-8">
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">1. Acceptance of Terms</h2>
        <p class="text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed">
          By accessing or using PkgWatch ("the Service"), you agree to be bound by these Terms of Service. If you do not agree to these terms, do not use the Service.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">2. Description of Service</h2>
        <p class="text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed">
          PkgWatch provides package health analysis for npm and PyPI packages. The Service includes an API, CLI tool, and GitHub Action that provide health scores, risk assessments, and abandonment predictions for open-source packages.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">3. Account Registration</h2>
        <p class="text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          To use certain features of the Service, you must register for an account. You agree to:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-zinc-400 space-y-2 ml-4">
          <li>Provide accurate and complete registration information</li>
          <li>Maintain the security of your API keys</li>
          <li>Notify us immediately of any unauthorized use of your account</li>
          <li>Accept responsibility for all activities under your account</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">4. Acceptable Use</h2>
        <p class="text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          You agree NOT to:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-zinc-400 space-y-2 ml-4">
          <li>Exceed your plan's rate limits or attempt to circumvent them</li>
          <li>Share, sell, or transfer your API keys to third parties</li>
          <li>Use the Service for any illegal purpose</li>
          <li>Attempt to reverse engineer, decompile, or extract our algorithms</li>
          <li>Interfere with or disrupt the Service or its infrastructure</li>
          <li>Scrape or bulk download data from the Service beyond normal API usage</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">5. API Usage and Rate Limits</h2>
        <p class="text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          The Service is provided with usage limits based on your subscription tier:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-zinc-400 space-y-2 ml-4">
          <li><strong class="text-zinc-300">Free:</strong> 5,000 requests per month</li>
          <li><strong class="text-zinc-300">Starter ($9/mo):</strong> 25,000 requests per month</li>
          <li><strong class="text-zinc-300">Pro ($29/mo):</strong> 100,000 requests per month</li>
          <li><strong class="text-zinc-300">Business ($99/mo):</strong> 500,000 requests per month</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed mt-4">
          Demo mode (without API key) is limited to 20 requests per hour per IP address. Requests exceeding your limit will be rejected with a 429 status code. We reserve the right to suspend accounts that consistently attempt to exceed limits or abuse the Service.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">6. Data and Accuracy</h2>
        <p class="text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          The Service provides health scores and risk assessments based on publicly available data. You acknowledge that:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-zinc-400 space-y-2 ml-4">
          <li>Scores are estimates and predictions, not guarantees</li>
          <li>Data may be delayed or incomplete due to upstream sources</li>
          <li>You should not rely solely on our scores for critical security decisions</li>
          <li>We are not responsible for decisions made based on our data</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">7. Intellectual Property</h2>
        <p class="text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed">
          The Service, including its algorithms, scoring methodology, and user interface, is protected by intellectual property laws. You retain ownership of any data you submit to the Service. We retain ownership of all aggregated, anonymized insights derived from Service usage.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">8. Payment Terms</h2>
        <p class="text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          For paid subscriptions: payments are processed through Stripe. Subscriptions renew automatically unless cancelled. You may cancel your subscription at any time through your dashboard; access continues until the end of the current billing period.
        </p>
        <p class="text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed">
          Refunds are not provided. For billing questions, contact <a href="mailto:support@pkgwatch.dev" class="text-blue-400 hover:underline">support@pkgwatch.dev</a>.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">9. Service Availability</h2>
        <p class="text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed">
          We strive to maintain high availability but do not guarantee uninterrupted service. We may modify, suspend, or discontinue the Service at any time with reasonable notice. Scheduled maintenance will be announced in advance when possible.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">10. Disclaimer of Warranties</h2>
        <p class="text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed">
          THE SERVICE IS PROVIDED "AS IS" WITHOUT WARRANTIES OF ANY KIND, EXPRESS OR IMPLIED, INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED TO WARRANTIES OF MERCHANTABILITY, FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE, AND NON-INFRINGEMENT. WE DO NOT WARRANT THAT THE SERVICE WILL BE ERROR-FREE OR UNINTERRUPTED.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">11. Limitation of Liability</h2>
        <p class="text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed">
          TO THE MAXIMUM EXTENT PERMITTED BY LAW, PKGWATCH SHALL NOT BE LIABLE FOR ANY INDIRECT, INCIDENTAL, SPECIAL, CONSEQUENTIAL, OR PUNITIVE DAMAGES, INCLUDING LOSS OF PROFITS, DATA, OR GOODWILL, ARISING FROM YOUR USE OF THE SERVICE.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">12. Termination</h2>
        <p class="text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed">
          We may terminate or suspend your account at any time for violation of these terms. Upon termination, your right to use the Service ceases immediately. You may terminate your account at any time by contacting us.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">13. Indemnification</h2>
        <p class="text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed">
          You agree to indemnify, defend, and hold harmless PkgWatch and its officers, directors, employees, and agents from any claims, damages, losses, liabilities, and expenses (including reasonable legal fees) arising from: (a) your use of the Service; (b) your violation of these Terms; (c) your violation of any third-party rights; or (d) any content you submit to the Service.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">14. Dispute Resolution</h2>
        <p class="text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          Before initiating any legal proceedings, you agree to first contact us at <a href="mailto:support@pkgwatch.dev" class="text-blue-400 hover:underline">support@pkgwatch.dev</a> and attempt to resolve the dispute informally for at least 30 days.
        </p>
        <p class="text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed">
          If we cannot resolve the dispute informally, any legal action must be filed in the courts of Portugal. You agree to waive any right to participate in a class action lawsuit or class-wide arbitration against PkgWatch.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">15. Force Majeure</h2>
        <p class="text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed">
          PkgWatch shall not be liable for any failure or delay in performance due to circumstances beyond our reasonable control, including but not limited to: acts of God, natural disasters, war, terrorism, riots, embargoes, acts of civil or military authorities, fire, floods, accidents, strikes, or shortages of transportation, facilities, fuel, energy, labor, or materials.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">16. Changes to Terms</h2>
        <p class="text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed">
          We may modify these terms at any time. Material changes will be communicated via email or prominent notice on the Service. Continued use after changes constitutes acceptance of the new terms.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">17. Governing Law</h2>
        <p class="text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed">
          These terms are governed by the laws of Portugal. Any disputes shall be resolved in the courts of Portugal.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">18. Contact</h2>
        <p class="text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed">
          For questions about these Terms of Service, contact us at <a href="mailto:support@pkgwatch.dev" class="text-blue-400 hover:underline">support@pkgwatch.dev</a>.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
</Layout>
